<p class="has-vivid-cyan-blue-color has-text-color has-link-color has-medium-font-size wp-elements-1c62b64346480a5c2fbf060d6346ab2a"><strong>About Management Trainee Vacancy in AIC:</strong></p>



<p class="">The Agriculture Insurance Company of India Limited (AIC) is a public sector undertaking headquartered in New Delhi. AIC is primarily involved in providing crop insurance to farmers across India. It is the leading implementing agency for the Pradhan Mantri Fasal Bima Yojana (PMFBY), a flagship crop insurance scheme launched by the Government of India. </p>



<p class="has-vivid-cyan-blue-color has-text-color has-link-color has-medium-font-size wp-elements-cb3f86062557e280ad2f319f930cfabc"><strong>Post Name, No. of Posts and Qualification:</strong></p>



<figure class="wp-block-table"><table class="has-cyan-bluish-gray-background-color has-background"><tbody><tr><td><strong>Post Name</strong></td><td><strong>No. of Post</strong></td><td><strong>Qualification</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Management Trainee (IT)</td><td>20<br><br></td><td>B. E / B.Tech / M.E. / M.Tech in Computer Science/Information Technology/ MCA<br>from a recognized University with minimum 60% marks in either of the degree<br>examination for UR/OBC/EWS &amp; 55% for SC/ST/PwBD candidates</td></tr><tr><td>Management Trainee (Actuarial)</td><td>05</td><td>Bachelor’s degree / Master’s degree in Statistics/ Mathematics/ Actuarial Sciences/<br>Economics/ Operations with minimum 60% marks for UR/OBC/EWS and 55% for<br>SC/ST/PwBD candidates.<br><strong>OR</strong><br>Bachelor’s/ Master’s degree in any discipline from a recognized University with<br>minimum 60% marks in either of the degree examination for UR/OBC/EWS and 55%<br>for SC/ST/PwBD candidates and credit of minimum 2 papers from Institute of<br>Actuaries of India (IAI)/ Institute and Faculty of Actuaries (IFoA), UK as per new<br>curriculum.</td></tr><tr><td>Management Trainee (Generalist)</td><td>30</td><td>Graduation / Post graduation in any discipline from a recognized<br>University with minimum 60% marks for UR/OBC/EWS candidates and minimum 55% marks for SC/ST/PwBD candidates in either of the degrees.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>



<p class="has-vivid-cyan-blue-color has-text-color has-link-color has-medium-font-size wp-elements-faf99a79ad1a88991eaf3e10582c0013"><strong>Age Limit for Management Trainee Vacancy in AIC:</strong></p>



<p class="">Minimum Age: 21 years &amp; Maximum Age: 30 years<br>i.e. a candidate must have been born not earlier than 2 nd December 1994 and not later than 1 st December 2003  (both dates inclusive). Age relaxation as per AIC rules.</p>



<p class="has-vivid-cyan-blue-color has-text-color has-link-color has-medium-font-size wp-elements-279ab11f2e1b9bc94362bb3242c9e1c3"><strong>Emoluments &amp; benefits:</strong></p>



<p class="">Rs. 60,000/- p.m. for the one year of training.</p>



<p class="">The trainee shall be eligible for the post of Administrative Officer (Scale I) on completion of the training period and subject to satisfactory work performance, Interview/Interaction and/or any other criteria as may be decided by the Company.</p>



<p class="has-vivid-cyan-blue-color has-text-color has-link-color has-medium-font-size wp-elements-6c04d80125e18eae439d6234ec15cb6c"><strong>Application Fee AIC Management Trainee:</strong></p>



<p class="">SC/ST/PwBD Rs. 200/- (Intimation charges only). All other categories Rs. 1000/- (application fee including intimation charges).</p>



<p class="has-vivid-cyan-blue-color has-text-color has-link-color has-medium-font-size wp-elements-a53626372f9197adf976dff039dc57b4"><strong>Selection Process of AIC Management Trainee in AIC:</strong></p>



<p class="">Selection would be based on the performance in the Online Examination and Interview. Shortlisted candidates in final merit list will have to undergo Pre-Recruitment Medical Examination. </p>



<p class="has-vivid-cyan-blue-color has-text-color has-link-color has-medium-font-size wp-elements-9d63a8c51a35cd795b3b8de2c9b9c5a8"><strong>Important Dates:</strong></p>



